      <h2>How to Choose Based on Your Trade</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Framers & Carpenters:</strong> Prioritize puncture resistance and ankle support. NINGO Steel Toe (4.6★) or Heavy Duty Steel Toe (4.4★) are top picks.</li>
        <li><strong>Concrete & Masonry Workers:</strong> Waterproofing is mandatory. NORTIV 8 ARMADILLO-STL (4.5★) is the clear winner here.</li>
        <li><strong>Roofers:</strong> Slip resistance + lightweight. NORTIV 8 TROOP (4.3★) or Furuian (4.2★) work well.</li>
        <li><strong>Electricians:</strong> EH rating + non-conductive toe. NINGO Steel Toe (EH rated) or NINGO Composite Toe.</li>
        <li><strong>HVAC Technicians:</strong> Comfort for all-day wear. Waterproof Soft Toe or NINGO Steel Toe for mixed environments.</li>
        <li><strong>Supervisors & Inspectors:</strong> Comfort and waterproofing over maximum protection. Waterproof Soft Toe Leather (4.5★).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
      <p>For most construction trades, the <strong>NINGO Steel Toe Work Boots</strong> (4.6★) offer the best combination of safety, comfort, and value. If you need waterproofing, go with the <strong>NORTIV 8 ARMADILLO-STL</strong>. On a tight budget? The <strong>Furuian Steel Toe Boots</strong> deliver solid protection for under $60.</p>
      <p>Remember: your boots are your most-used tool. Spending a little more on the right pair pays for itself in comfort, safety, and durability.</p>

